-- Smith Close to Four-Year Extension With Knicks, Daily News Says
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-07-04T04:12:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-04/smith-close-to-four-year-extension-with-knicks-daily-news-says.html
J.R. Smith is close to signing a
four-year extension that would put the New York Knicks’ top five
players under contract for next season,  the New York Daily News
reported , citing a person familiar with the talks.  Smith is expected to receive the “Average Player Salary
Exception,” which could amount to $24 million over four seasons,
the newspaper said.  Smith’s signature would see him join  Carmelo Anthony , Iman Shumpert,  Raymond Felton  and Tyson Chandler under contract with
the team.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
